name: Rapunzel (Tangled series)
description:
If you like the LoRa, please feel free to share your generated images here and leave a review (or at least a rating) for the sake of motivation and stuff ;D

For usage guidance, look into the About this version box for more information and click on Show more to get all trigger words and combinations (The trigger words in the Details box are a pain to manage).

Please contact me here on civitAi or on Twitter if you want to provide the LoRa in a generation service.

About

So I was watching the Tangeld movie the other day and wanted to make a LoRa out of it, but ran straight into the problem that she wears the same outfit all the time, which means it's pretty hard to get her to wear new clothes, but then I saw that there's actually a 3-session long animated series with a slightly different style, but dressed up enough, so I was hooked :D

Training

I collected 85 115 images for training, Rapunzel really wears a variety of costumes in the series, which is not featured in this version of LoRa yet.

modelVersions.name: v2.2
modelVersions.description:
skipped v2.1 because I accidentally forgot to apply the tags for training (result was really nice but no control over hair and trained outfits suck)

Changelog

  • Outfit improvements

  • complete overhaul of the hair tags

How to use the LoRa

Basic prompt, No weight adjustments required

rapunzel, purple princess outfit <lora:Rapunzel_v1:1>

If the somewhat unfortunate version of Pascal (The Green Chameleon) is generated with Rapunzel, put pascal into the negative prompt, it will also work the other way round, but be prepared for a somewhat ugly version of a chameleon that looks more like a frog most of the time. Use loose_hair to get her long hair, try playing with the multipliers (on 1.0 it most of the time still is braided)

use long_braid to get braided hair.

Green beach outfit

rapunzel, green island outfit <lora:Rapunzel_v1:1>

Adventure outfit

rapunzel, adventure outfit <lora:Rapunzel_v1:1> (tip: add purple princess outfit to negative prompt, on some checkpoints both outfits get mixed up (e.g. DreamShaper) )
